Timing is everything: Purchases made on Monday saw the highest rate of returns, indicating that buyer's remorse hit hardest at the start of the week

The site also revealed some interesting facts about how and when its customers shopped.

Wednesday evenings saw the most traffic in 2014, with French shoppers typically flocking to the site at 7pm, and New Yorkers and Londoners stopping in later at 9pm.

Purchases made on Monday saw the highest rate of returns, indicating that buyer's remorse hit hardest at the start of the week.

All in all, Lyst's customers spent over 68million minutes on the site in 2014; the equivalent of over 129 years collectively.

